        content: "A judge paradigm is a written statement where a judge explains how they evaluate debates. It's basically a cheat sheet telling you exactly what the judge wants to see. Learning to read and interpret paradigms is one of the most powerful skills in competitive debate.\n\nMost tournaments post judge paradigms online before the event, and many judges maintain paradigm statements on platforms like Tabroom or judge wikis. These documents vary wildly in length and detail — some are a single sentence, others are multi-page essays. Regardless of length, every paradigm contains clues about how to win.\n\nIn this lesson, you'll learn to decode paradigm statements, identify the key information they contain, and translate that information into actionable strategy. Think of it as learning to read a map before you enter unfamiliar territory — the paradigm tells you where the safe paths are and where the pitfalls lie.",
